This paper is about adapting parameters of a deep neural network for automatic speech recognition, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses Bayesian approaches and hierarchical priors, which are common topics in machine learning and statistics, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SD (Statistics and Data Analysis) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves hidden Markov models, which are commonly used in speech recognition, suggesting that cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses optimization techniques for deep models, which is a topic in neural networks, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category.
